{
  "stem": "13673.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she took me by the hand, and we went up to the third floor, where there was like a storage room, and she found this, this Hanukkah menorah.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she must have-- I mean, she must have known that it was there all along.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But she brought that out, and we actually had a Hanukkah.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I had a sheet with the songs on it and--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My first Hanukkah.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lit the candles.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yep.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He did return after, I think, it was seven or eight weeks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, he came home on my birthday, which is on the 28th of December.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- but he wasn't allowed to talk about Dachau, and he never did.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was very thin and very old-looking, and he had frostbite on his toes.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was bad, but it was good to have him back home again.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I think-- he was never the most cheerful of men, I mean, but he would crack a joke every now and then.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But after that, it was like everything was dead serious, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everything was so serious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, I don't know if you want me to talk about this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At this point, when my father was already in Dachau, my mother made the decision to have my name placed on the Kindertransport list.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was from that night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everything stems back to that night.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Kristallnacht, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[DRINKS] And she heard about this-- this, this was an organized plan to rescue as many children-- rescue-- to get children out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At that point, everybody knew that it was not good to stay there anymore.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the thing was to get the children out as fast as possible.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
